 and major study of how Protestant missions changed the history and destiny of a tribal community in one of the unlikeliest regions of South Asia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aAmerican Studies : Indigenous Studies. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology of Religion. 4aAsian Studies : India and South Asian Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : History of Religion. 4aSociology : Sociology of Religion. 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848583640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438485836423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438485836/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles